  "prompt": "How do I ask a smart and intelligent question?",
  "response": "To ask a smart and intelligent question, consider these tips:\n\n1. Be specific and clear\n- Clearly define what you want to know\n- Provide context\n- Avoid vague or overly broad questions\n\n2. Do some preliminary research\n- Show you've already tried to find information\n- Demonstrate basic understanding of the topic\n- Highlight specific areas where you need more insight\n\n3. Ask thoughtful, open-ended questions\n- Encourage detailed and nuanced responses\n- Avoid yes/no questions\n- Use words like \"how,\" \"why,\" and \"what\"\n\n4. Structure your question logically\n- Start with background information\n- Explain your current understanding\n- Clearly state what you want to learn\n\n5. Show genuine curiosity\n- Demonstrate interest in learning\n- Be respectful and humble\n- Avoid sounding confrontational\n\n6. Use proper grammar and spelling\n- Makes your question easier to understand\n- Shows you're serious about getting a good answer\n\n7. Consider the audience/expert you're asking\n- Tailor your question to their expertise\n- Use appropriate language and terminology\n\n8. Be concise\n- Remove unnecessary details\n- Get to the point quickly\n- Make your question easy to read and understand\n\nExample: \"I'm trying to understand quantum mechanics. After reading basic introductions, I'm confused about how quantum entanglement works. Could you explain the key principles in simple terms?\"",
